

This file contains a listing and description of each file contained 
in the GEM DOS 68K DEVELOPER KIT according to it's subdirectory.

Revised:  11/22/85



================================================================= 


\RCS

CARP.RSC  .......  Sample resource file for Carp
CARP.RSH  .......  C file from RCS with header from RSHDR
HELLO.ACC .......  Executable version of HELLO, the sample accesory.
HELLO.PRG .......  Executable version of HELLO, the sample application.
IMAGDRI.ICN .....  A sample icon, the Digital Research Logo
INSTALL.BAT .....  Batch file for initail toolkit installation
RCS.PRG  ........  Resource Construction Set version 1
RCS.RSC  ........  The resource file for RCS


\SAMPLES

ACCSTART.S  ..... Start up routine for accessories
CRMULDIV.S  ..... Mathematics routines used by XFORM
DEMO.BAT  ....... Batch file for building DEMO.PRG
DEMO.C .......... C source for DEMO
DEMO.H .......... Include file for DEMO.C generated by RCS
DEMO.INP  ....... DEMO input link file
DEMO.PRG  ....... Executable GEM sample application
DEMO.RSC  ....... Resource file for DEMO
DEMO.RSH  ....... C file from RCS with header from RSHDR
DESKACC.H  ...... specifys whether application or accessory
DESKACC0.H  ..... Include file used to specify application
DESKACC1.H  ..... Include file used to specify accessory
DOSASM.S  ....... Assembly code portion of DOSBIND
DOSBIND.C  ...... All DOS 2.x requests go through this module
DOSBIND.H  ...... Include file for DOSBIND.C
EXAMPLE.RSC  .... C file from RCS with header from RSHDR
EXAMPLE.RSH  .... Output from RCS for use with RSCREATE 
FARDRAW.S  ...... Links to user defined objects
GEMASM.S  ....... Assembly portion of GEMBIND
GEMBIND.C  ...... Bindings to all GEM AES
GEMBIND.H  ...... Include file for GEMBIND
HELLO.BAT  ...... Batch file for producing HELLO.PRG
HELLO.C  ........ Source code for sample accessory
HELLO.INP  ...... Input file for linker
HELLOACC.BAT  ... Batch file for creating HELLO as a desk acc
HELLOACC.INP  ... Input file for linker
INSTALL.BAT  .... Batch file for initial installation 
LONGASM.S  ...... Utility routines for portability
MACHINE.H  ...... Processor specific definitions
PORTAB.H  ....... Processor specific definitions
OBDEFS.H  ....... Include file of object definitions
PROSTART.S ...... Shrinks memory ; see INTRO68K.DOC
RSCREATE.BAT .... Batch file for creating RSCREATE
RSCREATE.C  ..... source utility, "hand" makes resource files
RSCREATE.INP  ... Input file to linker for building RSCREATE
RSHDR.C  ........ Utility file for insertion into .RSH files
RSRCLIB.H  ...... Include file used with RSCREATE
TCRTL.C  ........ Tiny C run-time library (STRLEN, STRCAT, STRCPY)
TCRTLASM.S  ..... Assembly portion of TCRTL
TCS.S  .......... Tiny C start, replaces S.O in ALCYON
TCSACC.S ........ Tiny C start, for accessories only
TGEMBIND.C  ..... Tiny GEM binings
TREEADDR.H  ..... Include file for access of object trees 
TVDIBIND.C  ..... Tiny VDI bindings
VDIASM.S  ....... Assembly portion of VDI bindings
VDIBIND.C  ...... Bindings to GEM VDI
VDIBIND.H  ...... Include file for VDIBIND
XFORM.BAT  ...... Batch file for creating XFORM
XFORM.C  ........ Sample GEM application demonstrates transform
XFORM.H  ........ Include file for use with XFORM
XFORM.INP  ...... Linker input file for XFORM
XFORM.PRG  ...... Executable version of XFORM
XFORM.RSC  ...... XFORM resource file 
XFORM.RSH  ...... C file from RCS with header from RSHDR
XLIB.C  ......... Library of functions used by XFORM
XLIB.H  ......... Include file for XLIB.C


\TOOLS

CHECK.PRG  ....... Utility used by batch files for filetype check
COMMAND.PRG  ..... Command Interpreter for GEM DOS
FORMAT.PRG  ...... Disk format utility
INSTALL.BAT  ..... Batch file for initial installation
SID.PRG  ......... Non-graphic symbolic instruction debugger
SIZE68.PRG  ...... Utility used to compute command file sizes 
TIME.PRG  ........ Time of day utility
TREE.PRG  ........ Displays directory paths on a specific drive
XREF.PRG  ........ Produces a cross-reference symbol table
AR68.PRG  ........ DR 68000 Archive utility
AS68.PRG  ........ DR 68000 assembler
AS68INIT  ........ Initializes the AS68 assembler
AS68SYMB.DAT  .... Output file created by AS68
C068.PRG  ........ C compiler modules
C168.PRG  ........ C compiler modules
CP68.PRG  ........ C compiler modules
DATE.PRG  ........ Utility to retrieve current date from system
DIFF.PRG  ........ Compares to files for differences
DUMP.PRG  ........ Memory Dump utility
FIND.PRG  ........ Looks for a string in an ASCII file
LINK68.PRG  ...... 68K Linker
LO68.PRG  ........ 68K Linker
NM68.PRG  ........ displays symbol table of OBJ or command file
RELMOD.PRG  ...... Converts CP/M-68K relocatable files to GEM DOS 
RELOC.PRG  ....... Takes a relocatable file and makes it absolute
SENDC68.PRG  ..... Produces Motorola S-records from a command file


\BAT

ASM.BAT  ......... Batch file for AS68 assembler
C.BAT  ........... Batch file used by C compiler
LC.BAT  .......... batch file for linking 
SETPATH.BAT  ..... Batch file used to set path from Command line
F.BAT  ........... Batch file evokes FORMAT from Desktop
F.INP  ........... Input file used by F.BAT contains disk drive info
INSTALL.BAT  ..... Batch file for initial installation

\KERMIT

KERMIT.PRG  ...... File transfer utility
KERMIT.C  ........ The device independent KERMIT code
KIOAST.C  ........ C specific code for the ATARI ST
KIOLGEM.C  ....... C specific code for the Lisa 2/5
KIOVGEM.C  ....... C specific code for the VME/10
RS2.C  ........... RS232 initialization code for the VME/10
KASMAST.S  ....... Assembly specific code for the ATARI ST
KASMLGEM.S  ...... Assembly specific code for the Lisa 2/5
KASMVGEM.S  ...... Assembly specific code for the VME/10
RS2.H  ........... Include file for RS2.C
AST.BAT  ......... Batch file to link KERMIT for the ATARI ST
LISAGEM.BAT  ..... Batch file to link KERMIT for the Lisa 2/5
VGEM.BAT  ........ Batch file to link KERMIT for the VME/10

\DOC

FILES.DOC  ....... ********   THIS  FILE   ********************
README.DOC  ...... Misc release notes for this kit,  READ THIS FILE!
INSTALL.DOC  ..... Batch file for initial toolkit installation
INTRO68K.DOC  .... An introduction to develoment with the 68K kit
XFORM.DOC  ....... doc for image transformation sample GEM app.


\MINI

ABEND.C  ......... Module to report error messages and terminate
BDOS.S  .......... BDOS interface for MINI Run Time Library
BIOS.S  .......... BIOS interface for MINI Run Time Library
M.BAT  ........... batch file for linking MINI 
MAKEMINI.BAT  .... Batch file to build MINI RTL
MINI.H  .......... Include file for MINI
MINIS.S  ......... Startup code for runtime library
MS.BAT  .......... batch file for linking MINI
PUT10W.C  ........ Put unsigned word decimal for MINI runtime library
PUTBYTE.C  ....... Put Byte for MINI runtime library
PUTLONG.C  ....... Put Long for MINI runtime library
PUTNIBBL.C  ...... Put Nibble for MINI runtime library
PUTWORD.C  ....... Put Word for MINI runtime library
STRCAT.C  ........ String concatenate for MINI runtime library
STRCPY.C  ........ String copy for MINI runtime library
STRLEN.C  ........ String length for MINI runtime library

\RUNTIME

ASSERT.H  ........ macro used for debugging
CLIB  ............ C runtime library
CTYPE.H  ......... Clasify ASCII-coded integers
ERRNO.H  ......... AES error codes
INSTALL.BAT  ..... Batch file for initial installation
LIBE.A  .......... C runtime library (use w/floating point), IEEE
LIBF.A  .......... C runtime library (use w/floating point), Motorola
OPTION.H  ........ disregards unused options of runtime libraries
OSATTR.H  ........ Defines O.S. specific abilities
OSFIX.H  ......... Structure definitions for O.S. interface
OSIF.H  .......... O.S. specific definitions for DRI CLEAR/C RTL
OSIFERR.H  ....... O.S. error handler definition
PORTAB.H  ........ Processor-specific definitions
S.O.  ............ startup module for use with run time libraries
SETJMP.H  ........ Function declaration for Long Jump routine
SGTTY.H  ......... TTY info include file
STDIO.H  ......... definitions for standard I/O
TIME.H  .......... structure definition of the output of TIME.PRG
